<doc id="801754" wikidata="Q2426448" url="?curid=801754" title="Andrey Arkhangelsky">
<text>Andrey Dmitriyevich Arkhangelsky () (December 8, 1879 – June 16, 1940) was a geologist. He was a professor at Moscow State University. He was Corresponding Member of the Division of Physical-Mathematical Sciences since 1925, and Academician of the Division of Physical-Mathematical Sciences since 1929.

He won the Lenin Prize in 1928.

==Memoria==
A crater on Mars and Arkhangel&#x27;skiy Nunataks in Antarctica are named after him.

